  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Analyze tender documents, drawings and specifications</li><li>Conduct quantity take off and estimate costs</li><li>Coordinate with suppliers and sub-contractors to prepare costing for tender submission</li><li>Prepare tender and supporting documents for submission</li><li>Follow up on any technical clarifications during post-tender stage</li><li>Attend site show rounds and tender interviews</li><li>Prepare sub-contractor agreement, work order and VO</li><li>Monitor project progress and control budget</li><li>Collaborate with Project Team to track work progress for claim submission to Main Contractor</li><li>Assess sub-contractor's monthly claims and prepare payment certificate/response</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree / Diploma in Building / Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 2-4 years experience in Construction, preferably in handling projects for building construction industry.</li><li>Knowledgeable of Singapore Standard local codes and regulations.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and written communication skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently while being a good team player.</li><li>Strong follow up and closure skills</li></ul>",
